      "writtenOn": "2026-03-24T17:10:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can\u0027t really reconcile their commit message with their diff.\n\nContent-Transfer-Encoding I think is actually just a bug in our code, and should probably just be omitted.  It was originally added to prevent executable injection attacks, but browsers have a better way to do that these days, Redfish added base64 inline in the log entry, so we could probably just drop the base64 stuff entirely.\n\nHTTP2-Settings, I have no idea why boost removed it.  Mozilla doesn\u0027t list it on the page linked\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Reference/Headers\n\nBut iana does\nhttps://www.iana.org/assignments/http-fields/http-fields.xhtml\n\nI can dig deeper later.",
